Privacy Policy for FamilyLink

Last updated: March 2026

FamilyLink ("we", "our", or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use the FamilyLink mobile application.

1. Information We Collect

When using the FamilyLink app we may collect the following information:

• Account information (name, username, phone number)
• Location data (only when location sharing is enabled)
• Device information
• App usage information

2. Location Information

FamilyLink allows family members to share their live location with each other. Location data is collected only when permission is granted by the user and is used solely for family location sharing within the app.

Location data is not sold or shared with third parties.

3. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information to:

• Provide family location sharing features
• Enable family invitations and connections
• Improve the app experience
• Maintain security of user accounts

4. Data Sharing

We do not sell or rent personal data. Information is only shared between connected family members within the application.

5. Data Security

We take reasonable security measures to protect your information and prevent unauthorized access.

6. Third-Party Services

FamilyLink may use third-party services such as:

• Supabase (for authentication and database services)

These services may collect limited information necessary to operate the app.

7. Children's Privacy

FamilyLink is designed for family use. Parents or guardians are responsible for supervising children's use of the application.

